comments: Horrible teacher. I did not learn ANYTHING. She\'s very vague on her description of the assignments. She\'s a part time teacher so her attention is not focused on this class. She takes forever to grade the assignments and although she said she is willing to help, she is never there. She\'s a CIS professor, she\'s always having technical difficulties.

Somehow I received a grade for the class through the GSU website, despite having 7 outstanding assignments that had still yet to be graded upon completion of the class. She seems interested in the subject matter, but does not devote any time to communication or grading. She made this class pretty aggravating and useless - which is a shame.
I agree with the previous comment!!!!!!!
Slow at getting grades back and responding to questions. Seemed to be very unorganized. I took the online summer course. Nice person overall, but not the best instructor.
Enjoyable class, very interesting online class where you have to be online during a specific time period as she holds class via Eluminate with audio and slide show. Overall good class.
Very nice Professor, CIS geek!! Will try to persuade you into the field of CIS, I would recommend her.
